              <tr> 
                <td class="chblue"><font class="h1font"> Advanced Decks</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">The Arderial - Ver. 6.0</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size=1>(4.29)</font> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=21544">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=9006">Bryan "Tymer" Howland</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=9006&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Developed around a Vellup/Xyx Madness swarm, <I>The Arderial</I> uses a solid Creature base to beatdown opposition with good Spell support.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> February 18, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Magi <I>(In order)</I>:<BR><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(898)">Delia</a> (Starting: <a href="javascript:card_browser(336)">Vellup</a>, <a href="javascript:card_browser(356)">Shooting Star</a>)<BR><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(528)">Sorreah</a> (Starting: Any two Arderial Spells, <a href="javascript:card_browser(670}<a href="javascript:card_browser({528)">Sorreah</a>&#39;s Dream</a>)<BR><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(344)">Ora</a> (Starting: <a href="javascript:card_browser(338}<a href="javascript:card_browser({337)">Xyx</a> Elder</a>, <a href="javascript:card_browser(339}<a href="javascript:card_browser({337)">Xyx</a> Minor</a>, <a href="javascript:card_browser(356)">Shooting Star</a>)<BR><br>
Creatures (19):<BR><br>
2 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(519)">Brannix</a><br>
2 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(520)">Flutter Yup</a><br>
2 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(661)">Elder <a href="javascript:card_browser(336)">Vellup</a></a><br>
2 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(330)">Lovian</a><br>
3 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(336)">Vellup</a><br>
3 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(337)">Xyx</a><br>
2 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(338}<a href="javascript:card_browser({337)">Xyx</a> Elder</a><br>
3 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(339}<a href="javascript:card_browser({337)">Xyx</a> Minor</a><BR><br>
Relics (8):<BR><br>
2 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(507)">Relic Stalker</a><br>
2 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(512)">Warrior&#39;s Boots</a><br>
2 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(652)">Rayje&#39;s Belt</a><br>
2 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(351)">Storm Ring</a><BR><br>
Spells (15):<BR><br>
2 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(790)">Beam of Light</a><br>
2 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(669)">Cataclysm</a><br>
2 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(532)">Cry of Thunder</a><br>
2 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(354)">Lightning</a><br>
2 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(355)">Shockwave</a><br>
1 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(356)">Shooting Star</a><br>
2 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(670}<a href="javascript:card_browser({528)">Sorreah</a>&#39;s Dream</a><br>
2 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(357)">Storm Cloud</a><BR><BR><br>
Total: 42 non-Magi cards   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> <B>History</B><BR><br>
As a Region, Arderial was the first Region I truely felt comfortable with when learning to play Magi-Nation Duel. <I>The Arderial</I> was one of my first solid, tournanament-level, decks. While this version bares almost nothing to it&#39;s eariler incarnations, I take great pride in it. <I>The Arderial</I>&#39;s main concept has always been some kind of disruption lead followed by a Xyx Swarm generated by Ora in the back slot. While the disruption method has varied version to version, I have always tried to make the best use of what ever disruption method I chose.<BR><br>
<B>How does the deck work?</B><BR><br>
This version of <I>The Arderial</I> works around some concepts that I saw discused in a article concerning the use of Sorreah as a finishing Magi and Cataclysm as the opening door to win with. While in concept this sounds good, I felt Sorreah worked well as a mid-slot Magi and had been using him in the mid-slot for <I>The Arderial</I> since Awakening has been out. In that article, the author proposed a deck using Delia/Ora/Sorreah for Magi and basing the deck around a Vellup/Xyx Swarm supported by Shockwaves, Storm Clouds, and Cataclysms. Most of the Spell elements and the Xyx elements I had already been working with, so it wasn&#39;t hard to retool the deck to work with this kind of theme.<br>
The early part of play revolves around keeping at least one Elder Vellup cycling Creautres out of your deck and into hand by allowing one Elder Vellup to die either in Creature Combat or by an Opponent&#39;s card, Recurring Dreams it back into hand <I>(usually durring your 1st P/S/R)</I>, and then playing either the retrived one or playing the other Elder Vellup you should have. While your doing this, your Vellups should be able to aid in the deck&#39;s defence. I realize that you can&#39;t spend the 6E every turn to keep a Elder Vellup cycled. All that you have to do is cycle an Elder Vellup as often as you can.<br>
Hopefully within 4 to 5 turns, you should of cleared several additional Creatures out of the deck, through the Elder Vellups, into your hand, as well as through your regular draws. Part of this deck relies on you <B>not</B> to play too many Spells early. This is improtamt as to allow you to get a Cataclysm when Sorreah comes up.<br>
Play your Spells with care. That way you may only need to grab one Arderial Spell <I>(Outside of a Sorreah&#39;s Dream)</I> from the discard pile and a much needed Cataclysm from the deck. If the way the match is going forces you to play a mulitiude of Spells, that&#39;s ok. Just keep recurring out either Vellups or Elder Vellups and stall. Sorreah, Cataclysm, and a well placed Xyx and Sorreah&#39;s Dream of Shock <I>should</I> be able to take out a Magi out right. Finally, Ora and her Xyx horde should work wonders with cleaning up whatever you will still have to face.<BR><br>
<B>The Magis</B><BR><br>
Delia - If you go first, just grab a Vellup and 4 random cards. I&#39;ve had decent luck pulling either a Shockwave or Storm Cloud in the opening Draw. As your playing out the Velup stuff, Don&#39;t necessarly get all three Vellups & one Elder Vellup. You might just wish to grab 2 Vellups & the Elder Vellup. That way you can always Recycle one of the Vellups, if it get&#39;s taken out on the opponent&#39;s turn, to grab the remaining Vellup <I>(and with it the other Elder Vellup)</I> on the next turn. With the first Elder Vellup, I usually go for a regular Xyx or a Lovian. That way I&#39;ve got something for later <I>(Xyx)</I> or something that will that I&#39;ll have as a secondary defensive measure <I>(Lovian)</I>.<BR><br>
Sorreah - Pretty much most of what I intend with Sorreah is mentioned above. If you can&#39;t get a Cataclysm with Sorreah, don&#39;t worry. Do the best you can to take out the current Magi and try and get the cataclysm for Ora.<BR><br>
Ora - While she doesn&#39;t seem to be the most powerfull of clean-up Magi, she has been able to win games for me with no difficulity. Always try and hold on to a Xyx and Sorreah&#39;s Dream, in addition to one extra Xyx Minor for when Ora comes up. That way you have options to potentially take out a Magi when she flips up.<BR><br>
<B>The Creatures</B><BR><br>
The six non-Vellup or non-Xyx Creatures might seem a little odd for this deck, but I think they fill out the Creature compliment nicely...<BR><br>
Brannix - 5E and capable of gaining energy when it attacks Creatures, it works. A good offensive Creature to compliment the deck.<BR><br>
Flutter Yup - It&#39;s a nice stall/speed bump Creature that can combo nicely along with a Storm Ring.<BR><br>
Lovian - It&#39;s Resistance Effect is the main reason Lovian is in the deck currently.<BR><br>
<B>The Spells</B><BR><br>
I think most of the Spells in the deck are pretty straight forward to understand as to why they are in the deck, but I thought I&#39;d spotlight a couple...<BR><br>
Sorreah&#39;s Dream - No matter what, <B>always</B> remember to grab a Sorreah&#39;s Dream when Sorreah filps up. Not only is it usefull with any of the Xyx family, but with any non-self referencing Power your Opponent might have in play. Also remember, that you can grab one Sorreah&#39;s Dream as a regular Starting card for Sorreah, but that you could also grab the other copy that&#39;s in the deck as one of the &#39;Any two Arderial Spells&#39; he starts with as well.<BR><br>
Cry of Thunder - Why this Spell instead of Solar Flare? It combos nicely with the Xyx family, as well as it&#39;s one of those Spells that You want to hold onto until just the right moment.<br>
Lightning and Shooting Star - Outside of the fact that they are decent staple Spells, I bet your wondering why I have them in here? Shooting Star is a Starting card for both Delia and Ora. While I may not always get it with Delia, I would rather have the optiion availabe to me, if needed. The Lightnings are nice for a little bit of Creature damage or boosting, if I need it.<BR><br>
<B>The Relics</B><BR><br>
I think all of the relics are pretty much self-explainatory as to why they are in the deck.<BR><br>
<B>Other Changes</B><BR><br>
After some extensive playing, I&#39;ve found that I could really use a third Elder Velup in the deck. I might take out one of the Brannixes out for third Elder Vellup.<br>
I&#39;ve also thought about adding one more card to the deck <I>(thus taking it to 43 non-Magi cards)</I>. It&#39;s either going to be a third Storm Ring or a third Warrior&#39;s Boots, but I haven&#39;t decided on that yet.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/magination/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=21544"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=21544" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/magination/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></td></tr></table></td>
